QUESTION 149) A children's toy is made up of a trailer and ten carts transported in it, according to the figure.
In the production sector of the company that manufactures this toy, all strollers are painted so that the appearance of the most attractive toy. Yellow, white, orange and green colors are used, and each cart is painted only with one color. The flag truck has a fixed color. The company determined that in every ceiling truck there must be at least one cart of each of the four colors available. Change of strollers in the flag truck does not generate a new model of the toy.
Based on this information, how many are the distinct models of the Truck Truck that this company can produce?
A) C6.4
B) C9.3
C) C10.4
D) 64
E) 46
